    "body": "See #38760\r\n\r\n## Problem\r\n\r\n- zipPlugin.vim, gzip.vim and tarPlugin.vim mostly share similar functionality and code\r\n- They mix multiple concerns: external tool invocation and editor integration (browsing UI, buffer integration)\r\n- Not reusable from Lua\r\n- Are synchronous\r\n\r\n## Solution\r\n\r\nFirst step is to create non-public infrastructure that has the same user-facing functionality as the 3 plugins. Later it can be decided if and how the interface should be public (e.g. under `vim.archive`).\r\n\r\nI'll probably start even smaller: just replace zipPlugin.vim for now. Later this can be extended with the right commands for tar and gzip.\r\n\r\nCloses: #38760\r\n",
    "closed_at": null,
